{
  "id": "019cdda6-6c6d-7e51-847b-a8943bb19282",
  "content": "# LinkedIn Carousel Production Workflow\n\n## Render Pipeline\nHTML/CSS → HTTP server (port 8099) → Playwright headless Chrome (2x deviceScaleFactor) → individual slide PNGs + multi-page PDF\n\n## Shared Tool\n`tools/carousel-render/render.js` — reusable render + validate script. Usage:\n```bash\nnode tools/carousel-render/render.js --url http://localhost:8099/path/to/carousel.html --outdir path/to/output\n```\n\nIncludes pre-flight checks (HTTP server, Chromium), renders PNGs + PDF, then validates: file sizes, text overflow, font minimums, content height budget.\n\n## Design System\n`docs/marketing/design-system.json` — canonical specs for carousel dimensions, typography scale, color palette. Both existing carousels (linux-discovery, ai-blind-designer) share these CSS custom properties.\n\n## Skill File\n`.agents/skills/visual-content-playwright.md` — teaches AI agents the correct workflow, common pitfalls, and design constraints for visual content production.",
